## Summary

Build a TtsService wrapper around `flutter_tts` that handles Korean and English speech output, selects the best available Korean voice per platform, and exposes state via Riverpod.

## Implementation Details

### 1. TtsService class

#### `lib/domain/services/tts_service.dart`

```dart
class TtsService {
  final FlutterTts _tts = FlutterTts();
  bool _isInitialized = false;

  Future<void> init() async {
    // Set default to Korean
    await _tts.setLanguage('ko-KR');
    await _tts.setSpeechRate(0.45);  // slower for learners
    await _tts.setPitch(1.0);
    await _tts.setVolume(1.0);

    // iOS: select best Korean voice
    if (Platform.isIOS) {
      final voices = await _tts.getVoices as List<dynamic>;
      // Prefer "Yuna" (highest quality Korean Siri voice)
      // Fallback to any ko-KR voice
      final koreanVoices = voices.where((v) =>
          (v['locale'] as String?)?.startsWith('ko') == true).toList();
      if (koreanVoices.isNotEmpty) {
        final yuna = koreanVoices.firstWhere(
          (v) => (v['name'] as String?)?.contains('Yuna') == true,
          orElse: () => koreanVoices.first,
        );
        await _tts.setVoice({
          'name': yuna['name'] as String,
          'locale': yuna['locale'] as String,
        });
      }
    }

    // Android: prefer Google TTS engine
    if (Platform.isAndroid) {
      final engines = await _tts.getEngines as List<dynamic>;
      if (engines.any((e) => e == 'com.google.android.tts')) {
        await _tts.setEngine('com.google.android.tts');
      }
    }

    _isInitialized = true;
  }

  /// Speak Korean text at learner-friendly speed
  /// [rate] 0.0-1.0, default 0.45 (slow). Use 0.7 for natural speed.
  Future<void> speakKorean(String text, {double rate = 0.45}) async {
    await _tts.setLanguage('ko-KR');
    await _tts.setSpeechRate(rate);
    await _tts.awaitSpeakCompletion(true);
    await _tts.speak(text);
  }

  /// Speak English text (for prompts like "How do you say...")
  Future<void> speakEnglish(String text) async {
    await _tts.setLanguage('en-US');
    await _tts.setSpeechRate(0.5);
    await _tts.awaitSpeakCompletion(true);
    await _tts.speak(text);
  }

  /// Stop any current speech
  Future<void> stop() async {
    await _tts.stop();
  }

  /// Whether TTS is currently speaking
  bool get isSpeaking => _isSpeaking;

  /// Stream of speaking state changes
  void setCompletionHandler(VoidCallback onComplete) {
    _tts.setCompletionHandler(onComplete);
  }

  void setStartHandler(VoidCallback onStart) {
    _tts.setStartHandler(onStart);
  }

  Future<void> dispose() async {
    await _tts.stop();
  }
}
```

### 2. Key design decisions

- **`awaitSpeakCompletion(true)`**: Makes `speak()` return a Future that completes when speech finishes. Critical for the drill engine to know when to transition from PRESENTING → WAITING state.
- **Speech rate 0.45**: Pimsleur starts slow and speeds up. The drill engine can increase rate as the learner progresses on an item.
- **Language switching**: The service switches between ko-KR and en-US as needed. Each `speak*` method sets the language explicitly to avoid state bugs.

### 3. Riverpod provider

```dart
final ttsServiceProvider = Provider<TtsService>((ref) {
  final service = TtsService();
  ref.onDispose(() => service.dispose());
  return service;
});

// Initialize in app startup
final ttsInitProvider = FutureProvider<void>((ref) async {
  final tts = ref.watch(ttsServiceProvider);
  await tts.init();
});
```

### 4. Platform considerations

**iOS:**
- Korean Siri voice "Yuna" is high quality and available on all modern iPhones
- On-device TTS works offline (no network needed)
- Must handle audio session category (may conflict with STT — see ticket #04)

**Android:**
- Google TTS Korean quality varies by device/TTS version
- Samsung devices have Samsung TTS which may be better — could detect and prefer it
- Some devices may not have Korean TTS data downloaded — `flutter_tts` will prompt user to install
- Consider calling `isLanguageAvailable('ko-KR')` on init and showing a message if unavailable

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] TtsService initializes and selects Korean voice on both platforms
- [ ] `speakKorean("감사합니다")` pronounces correctly
- [ ] `speakEnglish("How do you say thank you?")` works
- [ ] `awaitSpeakCompletion` correctly blocks until speech finishes
- [ ] Language switching between Korean and English works reliably
- [ ] Provider exposes service and handles disposal

**Phase:** 1 — Foundation (MVP)
**Blocked by:** #01
**Blocks:** #06

