## Summary

The core of the app. A state machine that orchestrates Pimsleur-style drill sessions: selects items, schedules them at graduated intervals, presents prompts via TTS, captures responses via STT, scores them, and provides feedback. This ticket implements prompted recall only (dialog simulation comes in Phase 4).

## Implementation Details

### 1. State machine

#### `lib/domain/services/drill_engine.dart`

```
States:
  idle           → no session active
  preparing      → building session queue from available items
  presenting     → TTS speaking the prompt
  waiting        → brief pause after prompt, before listening
  listening      → STT capturing user speech
  evaluating     → scoring user's response
  feedback       → showing result + correction
  sessionComplete → session finished, showing summary
  paused         → user paused mid-session

Transitions:
  idle → preparing         [startSession()]
  preparing → presenting   [session queue built, first item ready]
  presenting → waiting     [TTS finished speaking]
  waiting → listening      [after 500ms pause, STT starts]
  listening → evaluating   [STT returned result OR timeout]
  evaluating → feedback    [score computed]
  feedback → presenting    [user taps continue OR auto-advance after 3s, next item from queue]
  feedback → sessionComplete [no more items in queue]
  any → paused             [pauseSession()]
  paused → presenting      [resumeSession()]
  any → idle               [endSession()]
```

### 2. DrillEngineState

```dart
enum DrillEnginePhase {
  idle, preparing, presenting, waiting, listening, evaluating, feedback, sessionComplete, paused
}

class DrillEngineState {
  final DrillEnginePhase phase;
  final DrillItem? currentItem;
  final DrillEvaluation? lastEvaluation;
  final String? userResponse;      // what STT heard
  final int itemsCompleted;
  final int totalItems;
  final double sessionScore;       // running average
  final List<DrillItemResult> results; // completed items log
  final Duration sessionElapsed;   // active drill time

  // For the UI to know what to display
  bool get isVoiceActive => phase == DrillEnginePhase.presenting ||
                            phase == DrillEnginePhase.listening;
}

class DrillItemResult {
  final DrillItem item;
  final double score;
  final DrillResult result;
  final String? userResponse;
}
```

### 3. Pimsleur graduated interval scheduling

The core Pimsleur technique: new items are repeated at expanding intervals within a single session.

```dart
class DrillScheduler {
  /// Pimsleur in-session intervals
  static const pimsleurIntervals = [
    Duration.zero,               // 0. Introduction
    Duration(seconds: 5),        // 1. First recall
    Duration(seconds: 25),       // 2. Second recall
    Duration(minutes: 2),        // 3. Third recall
    Duration(minutes: 10),       // 4. Fourth recall
  ];

  /// Build the session timeline.
  ///
  /// [newItems] — items never seen before (repetitionCount == 0)
  /// [reviewItems] — items due for SRS review (nextReviewAt <= now)
  ///
  /// Returns a priority queue sorted by scheduled time.
  PriorityQueue<ScheduledDrill> buildSession({
    required List<DrillItem> newItems,
    required List<DrillItem> reviewItems,
    int maxNewItems = 5,
    int maxReviewItems = 15,
  }) {
    final queue = PriorityQueue<ScheduledDrill>();
    var sessionClock = Duration.zero;

    // Limit items
    final newBatch = newItems.take(maxNewItems).toList();
    final reviewBatch = reviewItems.take(maxReviewItems).toList();

    // Schedule new items with graduated intervals
    for (var i = 0; i < newBatch.length; i++) {
      final item = newBatch[i];
      // Stagger introductions so they don't all come at t=0
      final stagger = Duration(seconds: i * 15);

      for (var j = 0; j < pimsleurIntervals.length; j++) {
        queue.add(ScheduledDrill(
          item: item,
          scheduledAt: pimsleurIntervals[j] + stagger,
          isIntroduction: j == 0,
        ));
      }
    }

    // Schedule review items once at the start (interleaved with new items)
    for (var i = 0; i < reviewBatch.length; i++) {
      queue.add(ScheduledDrill(
        item: reviewBatch[i],
        scheduledAt: Duration(seconds: i * 10),
        isIntroduction: false,
      ));
    }

    return queue;
  }

  /// When an item is answered incorrectly, reschedule it sooner.
  ScheduledDrill rescheduleAfterFailure(DrillItem item, Duration currentTime) {
    return ScheduledDrill(
      item: item,
      scheduledAt: currentTime + const Duration(seconds: 15),
      isIntroduction: false,
    );
  }
}
```

**Session clock concept**: The "session clock" is cumulative active drill time, NOT wall clock time. If the user pauses the session, the clock stops. If item B is scheduled for t=25s but the user is still working on item A at t=25s, item B simply queues behind A. This matches how Pimsleur actually works — the intervals are approximate targets.

### 4. DrillEngine (Riverpod Notifier)

```dart
class DrillEngine extends Notifier<DrillEngineState> {
  late final TtsService _tts;
  late final SttService _stt;
  late final DrillEvaluator _evaluator;
  late final DrillScheduler _scheduler;
  late final ProgressRepository _progressRepo;

  PriorityQueue<ScheduledDrill>? _queue;
  final Stopwatch _sessionClock = Stopwatch();

  @override
  DrillEngineState build() {
    _tts = ref.read(ttsServiceProvider);
    _stt = ref.read(sttServiceProvider);
    _evaluator = ref.read(drillEvaluatorProvider);
    _scheduler = DrillScheduler();
    _progressRepo = ref.read(progressRepositoryProvider);
    return DrillEngineState.idle();
  }

  /// Start a new drill session
  Future<void> startSession() async {
    state = state.copyWith(phase: DrillEnginePhase.preparing);

    // Load items from DB
    final dueItems = await _progressRepo.getDueItemsWithContent();
    final allItems = await ref.read(lessonRepositoryProvider).getAllItems();

    // Separate new vs review
    final dueItemIds = dueItems.map((d) => d.item.id).toSet();
    final newItems = allItems
        .where((item) => !dueItemIds.contains(item.id))
        .map((item) => _createDrillItem(item, null))
        .toList();
    final reviewItems = dueItems
        .map((d) => _createDrillItem(d.item, d.progress))
        .toList();

    _queue = _scheduler.buildSession(
      newItems: newItems,
      reviewItems: reviewItems,
    );

    _sessionClock.start();
    await _presentNext();
  }

  /// Present the next item from the queue
  Future<void> _presentNext() async {
    if (_queue == null || _queue!.isEmpty) {
      _sessionClock.stop();
      state = state.copyWith(phase: DrillEnginePhase.sessionComplete);
      return;
    }

    final scheduled = _queue!.removeFirst();
    final item = scheduled.item;

    state = state.copyWith(
      phase: DrillEnginePhase.presenting,
      currentItem: item,
      lastEvaluation: null,
      userResponse: null,
    );

    // Speak the prompt
    if (scheduled.isIntroduction) {
      // For new items: say English, then Korean, then English again
      await _tts.speakEnglish(item.promptEnglish);
      await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 500));
      await _tts.speakKorean(item.expectedKorean, rate: 0.35);
      await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 500));
      await _tts.speakKorean(item.expectedKorean, rate: 0.45);
      // After introduction, move to next item (no user response needed)
      await Future.delayed(const Duration(seconds: 1));
      await _presentNext();
      return;
    }

    // For recall: speak English prompt, then listen
    await _tts.speakEnglish(item.promptEnglish);

    // Transition to waiting
    state = state.copyWith(phase: DrillEnginePhase.waiting);
    await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 500));

    // Start listening
    state = state.copyWith(phase: DrillEnginePhase.listening);
    final response = await _stt.listenForKorean();

    // Evaluate
    state = state.copyWith(
      phase: DrillEnginePhase.evaluating,
      userResponse: response,
    );

    if (response == null || response.isEmpty) {
      // No response — treat as fail
      final evaluation = DrillEvaluation(
        score: 0.0,
        result: DrillResult.fail,
        feedback: 'No response heard. The answer is: ${item.expectedKorean}',
      );
      await _handleEvaluation(item, evaluation);
    } else {
      final evaluation = _evaluator.evaluate(
        expected: item.expectedKorean,
        actual: response,
      );
      await _handleEvaluation(item, evaluation);
    }
  }

  Future<void> _handleEvaluation(DrillItem item, DrillEvaluation evaluation) async {
    item.score = evaluation.score;
    item.result = evaluation.result;

    state = state.copyWith(
      phase: DrillEnginePhase.feedback,
      lastEvaluation: evaluation,
      itemsCompleted: state.itemsCompleted + 1,
    );

    // Update progress in DB
    await _updateProgress(item, evaluation);

    // If failed, reschedule sooner
    if (evaluation.result == DrillResult.fail) {
      _queue!.add(_scheduler.rescheduleAfterFailure(
        item,
        _sessionClock.elapsed,
      ));
    }

    // Speak correct answer on failure
    if (evaluation.result != DrillResult.pass) {
      await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 500));
      await _tts.speakKorean(item.expectedKorean, rate: 0.4);
    }
  }

  /// User taps "continue" or auto-advance after feedback
  Future<void> continueAfterFeedback() async {
    await _presentNext();
  }

  /// Request a hint for the current item
  String? requestHint() {
    return state.currentItem?.nextHint;
  }

  void pauseSession() {
    _sessionClock.stop();
    _stt.stop();
    _tts.stop();
    state = state.copyWith(phase: DrillEnginePhase.paused);
  }

  void resumeSession() {
    _sessionClock.start();
    _presentNext();
  }

  void endSession() {
    _sessionClock.stop();
    _stt.stop();
    _tts.stop();
    state = DrillEngineState.idle();
  }

  Future<void> _updateProgress(DrillItem item, DrillEvaluation eval) async {
    // Simple progress update for MVP — full SM-2 comes in ticket #13
    final now = DateTime.now();
    final newCount = item.progress.repetitionCount + 1;
    await _progressRepo.updateProgress(UserProgress(
      itemId: item.lessonItem.id,
      easeFactor: item.progress.easeFactor,
      intervalSeconds: item.progress.intervalSeconds,
      nextReviewAt: now.add(const Duration(hours: 1)), // simple for MVP
      repetitionCount: newCount,
      lastScore: eval.score,
      lastReviewedAt: now,
    ));
  }

  DrillItem _createDrillItem(LessonItem item, UserProgress? progress) {
    return DrillItem(
      lessonItem: item,
      progress: progress ?? UserProgress(
        itemId: item.id,
        nextReviewAt: DateTime.now(),
      ),
      drillType: DrillType.promptedRecall,
      promptEnglish: 'How do you say "${item.english}" in Korean?',
      expectedKorean: item.korean,
      hints: _generateHints(item.korean),
    );
  }

  /// Generate progressive hints from Korean text
  List<String> _generateHints(String korean) {
    if (korean.isEmpty) return [];
    final chars = korean.characters.toList();
    if (chars.length <= 1) return [korean];
    return [
      '${chars.first}...',
      '${chars.take((chars.length / 2).ceil()).join()}...',
      korean,
    ];
  }
}
```

