### 3. Integration into DrillEngine

Modify `DrillEngine.startSession()`:

```dart
Future<void> startSession() async {
  state = state.copyWith(phase: DrillEnginePhase.preparing);

  // Load items + progress from DB
  final items = await _lessonRepo.getAllItems();
  final progress = await _progressRepo.getAllProgress();

  // Try Claude API for intelligent planning
  DrillPlan? plan;
  try {
    plan = await _claudeClient.generateDrillPlan(
      items: items,
      progress: progress,
    );
  } catch (e) {
    // Fallback to local scheduling if API unavailable
    // (uses the existing DrillScheduler from ticket #06)
  }

  if (plan != null) {
    // Build queue from Claude's plan
    _queue = _buildQueueFromPlan(plan, items, progress);
  } else {
    // Fallback: use local scheduler
    _queue = _scheduler.buildSession(newItems: ..., reviewItems: ...);
  }

  _sessionClock.start();
  await _presentNext();
}

PriorityQueue<ScheduledDrill> _buildQueueFromPlan(
  DrillPlan plan,
  List<LessonItem> items,
  List<UserProgress> progress,
) {
  final itemMap = {for (final i in items) i.id: i};
  final progressMap = {for (final p in progress) p.itemId: p};
  final queue = PriorityQueue<ScheduledDrill>();

  for (final planned in plan.sessionItems) {
    final lessonItem = itemMap[planned.itemId];
    if (lessonItem == null) continue;

    final drillItem = DrillItem(
      lessonItem: lessonItem,
      progress: progressMap[planned.itemId] ?? UserProgress(
        itemId: planned.itemId,
        nextReviewAt: DateTime.now(),
      ),
      drillType: DrillType.promptedRecall,
      promptEnglish: planned.promptEnglish,     // Claude's natural prompt
      expectedKorean: planned.expectedKorean,
      hints: planned.hintLevels,                // Claude's contextual hints
    );

    queue.add(ScheduledDrill(
      item: drillItem,
      scheduledAt: Duration(seconds: planned.scheduledDelaySeconds),
      isIntroduction: planned.isIntroduction,
    ));
  }

  return queue;
}
```

### 4. Graceful degradation

If the Claude API is unavailable (network error, rate limit, timeout):
- Fall back to the local `DrillScheduler` from ticket #06
- Use hardcoded prompt template: `"How do you say '{english}' in Korean?"`
- Use locally-generated hints from Korean text
- Log the failure for debugging
- Show a subtle indicator on the drill screen: "Offline mode"

This ensures the app always works, even without internet.

### 5. Caching

Cache the last successful drill plan in local storage. If the API fails on next session start, use the cached plan (with items re-shuffled) as a better fallback than the purely local scheduler.

