### 5. Loading dialogs from database

```dart
// In LessonRepository or a new DialogRepository:
Future<List<DialogDrillItem>> getDialogsForDrill() async {
  final dialogs = await db.select(db.dialogScripts).get();
  final result = <DialogDrillItem>[];

  for (final dialog in dialogs) {
    final turns = await (db.select(db.dialogTurns)
          ..where((t) => t.dialogId.equals(dialog.id))
          ..orderBy([(t) => OrderingTerm.asc(t.turnOrder)]))
        .get();

    // Create a DrillItem for the dialog as a whole
    // Use the first student turn as the "representative" lesson item
    result.add(DialogDrillItem(
      lessonItem: _dialogToLessonItem(dialog),
      progress: await _getOrCreateProgress(dialog.id),
      dialogId: dialog.id,
      dialogTitle: dialog.title,
      turns: turns.map(_toDialogTurn).toList(),
      promptEnglish: dialog.title,
      expectedKorean: '', // set per-turn
    ));
  }

  return result;
}
```

### 6. Handling incorrect responses mid-dialog

If the user fails a turn:
- Show the correct response
- TTS speaks the correct Korean
- Optionally: repeat the tutor's line and let user try again (max 1 retry per turn)
- Continue the dialog regardless (don't get stuck)

The overall dialog score is the average of all turn scores. If the dialog scores < 0.6, reschedule it sooner.

