## Summary

Ensure the app works fully offline for drill sessions and queues any data that needs to sync when connectivity returns.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Offline drill capability

Drills should work entirely offline:
- Lesson items are stored locally in Drift
- TTS: iOS supports offline Korean TTS. Android may require pre-downloading the Korean voice pack. Detect and prompt on first launch.
- STT: iOS supports offline Korean recognition on iPhone 12+ (iOS 15+). Android requires network — show a warning if offline and fall back to text input mode.
- DrillEngine uses local scheduler (no Claude API call) when offline
- DrillEvaluator uses local jamo scoring only (no Claude evaluation)

### 2. Network state detection

```dart
// Use connectivity_plus package
final connectivityProvider = StreamProvider<ConnectivityResult>((ref) {
  return Connectivity().onConnectivityChanged;
});

final isOnlineProvider = Provider<bool>((ref) {
  final connectivity = ref.watch(connectivityProvider);
  return connectivity.when(
    data: (result) => result != ConnectivityResult.none,
    loading: () => true,
    error: (_, __) => false,
  );
});
```

### 3. Sync queue for progress uploads

When offline, queue progress updates:

```dart
class SyncQueue {
  final AppDatabase db;

  // Add a pending_sync table to Drift:
  // pending_syncs: id, type (progress|session), payload (JSON), createdAt

  Future<void> enqueueProgressUpdate(UserProgress progress) async {
    await db.insertPendingSync(PendingSyncsCompanion(
      id: Value(const Uuid().v4()),
      type: const Value('progress'),
      payload: Value(jsonEncode(progress.toJson())),
      createdAt: Value(DateTime.now()),
    ));
  }

  Future<void> processQueue(SyncClient client) async {
    final pending = await db.getPendingSyncs();
    for (final item in pending) {
      try {
        if (item.type == 'progress') {
          final progress = UserProgress.fromJson(jsonDecode(item.payload));
          await client.uploadProgress([progress]);
        }
        await db.deletePendingSync(item.id);
      } catch (e) {
        // Leave in queue for retry
        break; // stop processing if network is down
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 4. Auto-sync on reconnect

```dart
final autoSyncProvider = Provider<void>((ref) {
  ref.listen(isOnlineProvider, (prev, next) {
    if (prev == false && next == true) {
      // Came back online — process sync queue
      ref.read(syncQueueProvider).processQueue(ref.read(syncClientProvider));
      // Also pull new content
      ref.invalidate(syncOnLaunchProvider);
    }
  });
});
```

