## Summary

Pre-generate and cache TTS audio for known lesson items to reduce latency during drills and enable better offline support on Android. Optionally use higher-quality cloud TTS for cached items.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Audio cache manager

#### `lib/domain/services/audio_cache.dart`

```dart
class AudioCacheManager {
  final Directory _cacheDir;

  AudioCacheManager(this._cacheDir);

  /// Get cached audio file path for a Korean text string.
  /// Returns null if not cached.
  String? getCachedPath(String koreanText) {
    final hash = _hashText(koreanText);
    final file = File('${_cacheDir.path}/tts_cache/$hash.mp3');
    return file.existsSync() ? file.path : null;
  }

  /// Cache audio data for a Korean text string.
  Future<String> cacheAudio(String koreanText, Uint8List audioData) async {
    final hash = _hashText(koreanText);
    final dir = Directory('${_cacheDir.path}/tts_cache');
    if (!dir.existsSync()) dir.createSync(recursive: true);
    final file = File('${dir.path}/$hash.mp3');
    await file.writeAsBytes(audioData);
    return file.path;
  }

  /// Pre-cache all lesson items using device TTS.
  Future<void> preCacheItems(List<LessonItem> items, TtsService tts) async {
    for (final item in items) {
      if (getCachedPath(item.korean) != null) continue;
      // Use flutter_tts synthesizeToFile if available
      // Otherwise skip — will use live TTS
      final path = '${_cacheDir.path}/tts_cache/${_hashText(item.korean)}.wav';
      await tts.synthesizeToFile(item.korean, path);
    }
  }

  /// Clear cache
  Future<void> clearCache() async {
    final dir = Directory('${_cacheDir.path}/tts_cache');
    if (dir.existsSync()) await dir.delete(recursive: true);
  }

  /// Cache size in bytes
  Future<int> getCacheSize() async {
    final dir = Directory('${_cacheDir.path}/tts_cache');
    if (!dir.existsSync()) return 0;
    int size = 0;
    await for (final entity in dir.list()) {
      if (entity is File) size += await entity.length();
    }
    return size;
  }

  String _hashText(String text) {
    return sha256.convert(utf8.encode(text)).toString().substring(0, 16);
  }
}
```

### 2. TtsService integration

Update TtsService to check cache before speaking:

```dart
Future<void> speakKorean(String text, {double rate = 0.45}) async {
  final cachedPath = _cacheManager?.getCachedPath(text);
  if (cachedPath != null) {
    // Play cached audio file instead of live TTS
    await _audioPlayer.play(DeviceFileSource(cachedPath));
    return;
  }
  // Fall back to live TTS
  await _tts.setLanguage('ko-KR');
  await _tts.setSpeechRate(rate);
  await _tts.awaitSpeakCompletion(true);
  await _tts.speak(text);
}
```

Requires `audioplayers` package for playing cached files:

```bash
flutter pub add audioplayers
```

